Objective

Ensure the equipment achieves the accuracy required at all time, support and perform calibration / verification for a wide range of Chemical, Physical and Optical laboratory equipment, as well as equipment purchasing, intermediate check, repair, and maintenance.

Your Responsibilities

Schedule and perform equipment calibration, verification, intermediate check, repair and maintenance, by following the calibration standards and requirement;
Prepare and review calibration procedures, measurement uncertainty and internal calibration reports to fulfill ISO/IEC 17025 requirements;
Co-ordinate with internal laboratory and calibration laboratory for internal/external calibration;
Manage the status and stock of laboratory’s equipment. Co-ordinate with supplier for sourcing and purchasing new equipment;
Maintain equipment record;
Simple office facilities maintenance;
Handle other equipment related tasks for quality assurance issues, such as internal/external auditing, document control, quality improvement projects, etc.
Maintain document control system;
Handle internal audit administration supporting tasks

The Skills We’re Looking For

Higher diploma / associate degree / degree holder of physics, mathematics or relevant engineering discipline;
Basic understanding of ISO/IEC 17025 quality system document;
Good communication skills and interpersonal skills;
Good trouble shooting skills;
Experiences of working in testing laboratory or toy industry is preferred;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Self-motivated and detail-minded;
Analytical mind and logical thinking;
Strong technical knowledge;
Fresh graduate is also welcome.
Other Benefits:

5-day work, public holidays
Performance bonus and year-end bonus
Medical and dental insurance
OT allowance
Annual Leave, Compensation Leave, Compassionate Leave

Responsibilities:

To support in developing, implementing and maintaining the documentation and quality assurance system of the company, including the standard operating procedures (SOPs);
To ensure the adequate records are maintained for controlling and monitoring conformity to specified GMP and statutory requirements;
To support the routine QA Department functions, including GMP training, self-inspection, line clearance;
Knowledge in Quality Management System (e.g change control, risk assessment and CAPA) is an advantage.

 Requirements:

Higher Diploma or University graduate in Pharmaceutical Studies / Food science/science related discipline;
Attention to details, hard-working and being able to work under pressure;
Strong communication skill, good command of English and Chinese;

We offer attractive remuneration package including medical scheme, discretionary year-end bonus etc. Interested parties please send full resume with salary expectation and availability by click "Apply Now". Only shortlisted candidates will be interviewed.

