Job Responsibilities

Assist in implementing and maintaining the documentation system and quality management system;
Assist in 1st, 2nd and 3rd parties audit, qualification, validation of equipment and facility;
Assist in handling customer complaints, conducting root cause analysis and following up corrective actions;
Provide training to employees to raise their awareness on quality requirements from customers and company;
Regular on site audit and checking
Assist in other ad-hoc projects as assigned.

 Job Requirements

Diploma holder in Quality Assurance or Science related disciplines
Minimum 1 year’s relevant experience, preferred in Logistics industry;
Knowledge in ISO 9001 standards is a must;
Professional certification in quality management system will be an advantage;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to be able to work well in a cross-functional team setting;
Detail-minded, self-motivated and proactive;
Proficiency in MS Office applications and Chinese word processing;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Fresh graduates will also be considered if of high caliber

We offer competitive salary, discretionary bonus, medical insurance, life and personal accident insurance, annual leave and staff purchase discount to the successful candidate. Interested candidates please send your resume with salary expectation by clicking "Apply Now".

