Job Duties:

Participate in manufacturing & quality control of In-vitro diagnosis reagents;
Monitor and review of manufacturing and quality control process;
Coordinate with multi-functional teams for new product launching;
Perform materials sourcing and quality control of incoming materials;
Review and update standard operation procedure and documents;
Provide technical training to ensure strictly follows to the approved SOP;
Assist in QMS accreditation and product registration;
Plan and perform stability study of new products;
Monitor and maintenance production facility and equipment.

Requirements:

Postgraduate, degree or diploma holder in life science or related discipline with knowledge in molecular genetics / molecular biology;
1 year of manufacturing experience in pharmaceutical, medical device or health care products;
Experienced in PCR or molecular lab is preferred;
Experience in handling equipment maintenance and calibration work;
Knowledge in ISO 9001, ISO 13485 or GMP / six sigma is an advantage;
Good written and verbal communication skills;
Good problem solving skill and able to work under pressure;
Team player attitude, proactive and self-motivated.

If you are passionate, driven and looking for a new and exciting opportunity within a successful and growing company, this may be the right role for you.

